-- PRESS DIGEST - Bulgaria - Aug 20
-- 
-- Wed Aug 20, 2014 03:06AM EDT
-- None



SOFIA, Aug 20 (Reuters) - These are some of the main stories in Bulgarian newspapers on Wednesday. Reuters has not verified these stories and does not vouch for their accuracy.

-- An unnamed fund, based in Vienna, has shown interest in rescuing troubled Corporate Commercial Bank (Corpbank) [6C9.BB], Interim Prime Minister Georgi Bliznashki said, adding the fund's officials will present a concrete plan within 10 days (Trud, Standart, Sega, Presa, Capital daily). -- A woman has died and another one was seriously injured in an accident with an elevator in a 12-storey residential building in capital Sofia, the interior ministry said (Trud, Standart, Sega, Presa, Monitor). -- Interim Foreign Minister Daniel Mitov warned of risk for Bulgaria of refugee influx due to conflict in Iraq. According to him, the critical situation in Iraq is the result of the West's indecisive actions in Syria over the past three years (Presa, Monitor). -- The interior ministry said Bulgaria should construction additional 131-km barbed wire fence at the border with its southeastern neighbour Turkey to save security costs. The Balkan country already completed a 33-km fence as it tries to cope with asylum seekers (Trud, Standart, Sega, Presa, Monitor). -- Kiril Ananiev, who served as deputy finance minister in charge of drafting the state budget in three successive governments from 1998 to 2009, was appointed Deputy Finance Minister in the interim government led by Prime Minister Georgi Bliznashki (Capital daily, Monitor).